                              <p>DANGER: Electric Shock</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Lockout tagout</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <p>Before starting maintenance on a motor</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Disconnect the motor from its power supply.</li>
                  <li>Switch off the power.</li>
                  <li>Lockout-tagout-verify the power supply to prevent it from being switched on
                     before work is completed.</li>
                  <li>If needed, turn off power to neighboring motors.</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Maintain motors according to the manufacturer's instructions.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>If the run-out distance is too great when stopping the motors, readjust the brakes
               ac- cording to the manufacturer's instructions.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Check the oil every 3,000 operating hours, or every 6 months at the latest.</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Review the SDS before using the oil.</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Change the oil at the motors or gears every 12,000 operating hours, or every 3
               years at the latest.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Ensure that the cooling air of external air-cooled motors always have efficient
               access to the cooling ribs. </p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Keep the cooling air routes in the area of the motors clean.</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
